@startuml
' Filename: OverallSimulation.plantuml
' Diagram Type: Component Diagram (top-level system context)
' Authored 2026-07-18 from the live engine:
'   scripts/simulation-server.mjs (tick loop + broadcast + client registry),
'   docs/infrastructure/DISTRIBUTED_SIMULATION_DESIGN.md (wire protocol),
'   docs/colloquy/AUTONOMOUS_AGENTS_ARCHITECTURE.md (unit taxonomy + per-tick server loop).
'
' One authoritative Simulation Server runs the Agent-Based Model at 20 Hz over
' N Units (Males on the shared Beam, floor-fixed Females) coupled through the
' Environment's light + sound channels. Each tick it broadcasts ONE canonical
' state frame (behavioral) over WebSocket to a read-only fan-out of clients.

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

' ===== The single authority ==================================================
package "Simulation Server (authoritative) — scripts/simulation-server.mjs" #e6fcc1 {

    ' The tick loop: sim.step(1) -> sim.getSnapshot() every TICK_MS (50 ms, 20 Hz).
    ' Ordered per-tick stages, from AUTONOMOUS_AGENTS_ARCHITECTURE.md section 6.
    component "Tick Loop @ 20 Hz\n(absolute-deadline scheduler)" as TickLoop #e6fcc1

    component "ABM Engine\n(sim-harness.ts)" as ABM #e6fcc1 {
        ' N Units resolved from the active scene graph topology.
        component "Males (x2)\non the shared Beam" as Males
        component "Females (x3)\nfloor / plinth-fixed" as Females
        component "Beam (x1)\narbitrated by dominant-drive Male" as Beam
    }

    ' Coupling medium: FOV intersection tests carry signal between units.
    component "Environment\nlight channel + sound channel" as Environment

    ' Canonical per-tick output: ONE state frame (behavioral) — the single
    ' source of truth every client projects.
    component "Canonical State Frame\n(behavioral: males / females / beam / env)" as Frame #e6fcc1

    component "Client Registry\n(clientId, role, canControl)" as Registry
    component "HTTP /status\n(health + per-client transport counters)" as Status
}

' Per-tick stages inside the loop (labels are the section-6 stage names).
TickLoop --> ABM : 1 advance physics (oscillators)\n2 world transforms
ABM --> Environment : 3 FOV intersection tests\n(microphone<->speaker, light_sensor<->light_source/beam)
Environment --> ABM : received signal per sensor
TickLoop --> ABM : 4 decode signals  5 drive model\n6 engagement FSMs  7 actuator outputs\n8 indicator states
Males --> Beam : Motion Request (Stop / Release) + drive level
ABM --> Frame : 9 collect changed frame vars
TickLoop --> Frame : reads snapshot each tick

' ===== The wire ==============================================================
interface "WebSocket /simulation\nhello / snapshot / patch\nping <-> pong / registry-status\n(frameDelta: keyframe + delta)" as Wire

Frame --> Wire : 10 broadcast
Registry -up-> Wire : registry-status
Status ..> Registry : reads

' ===== Read-only client fan-out =============================================
package "Read-only clients (many; no impact on sim fidelity)" #e4fcfa {
    component "Display Client\n(role viewer, Three.js projection)" as Display #e4fcfa
    component "Simulation Console\n(/simulation-console/ — registry, health, event log)" as Console #e4fcfa
    component "Actuator / Servo Client\n(phygital: drives Dynamixel from the frame)" as Actuator #e4fcfa
    component "Sensor Client\n(phygital: webcam / torch)" as Sensor #e4fcfa
    component "Transmitter Client\n(phygital)" as Transmitter #e4fcfa
}

Wire --> Display : snapshot + patch\n(announce role=viewer)
Wire --> Console : patch + registry-status
Wire --> Actuator : patch (latest-wins presentation)
Wire --> Transmitter : patch

' Sensor ingress: external samples feed the shared authority (operator-gated).
Sensor ..> Wire : sensor_input (external sense ingress)

' ===== The operator (mutating, gated) =======================================
actor "Operator\n(Scene Studio admin)" as Operator
Operator ..> Wire : set_scene_graph / load_scene_key /\nload_simulation_package / simulation_control\n(requires SIM_OPERATOR_TOKEN -> canControl)

legend right
  <b>Top-level system context (2026-07-18).</b>
  - ONE authority: the server owns physics, sensing, drives, engagement FSMs,
    actuation; clients only read + render. Any number of read-only clients
    connect with no effect on simulation fidelity.
  - The per-tick output is ONE canonical state frame carried on the wire as
    `behavioral` (males / females / beam / env). Delta-capable clients receive
    keyframe + frameDelta (approx 85-89% smaller); others get the full frame.
  - Tick rate: TICK_RATE 20 Hz (TICK_MS 50), absolute-deadline scheduler.
  - Mutating messages (set_scene_graph, load_scene_key,
    load_simulation_package, simulation_control, sensor_input) require the
    operator capability (SIM_OPERATOR_TOKEN -> canControl); every other socket
    is read-only.
  Sources: scripts/simulation-server.mjs;
  docs/infrastructure/DISTRIBUTED_SIMULATION_DESIGN.md;
  docs/colloquy/AUTONOMOUS_AGENTS_ARCHITECTURE.md.
endlegend

@enduml
